<TITLE> Six die in road crashes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 14 (bdnews24.com)  At least six people were killed and nine injured in separate road accidents in Narsinghdi and Chandpur on Monday. bdnews24.com Narsinghdi correspondent reported that four people died and seven were others injured after their Narsinghdi-bound pickup van hit a standing truck on the Dhaka-Sylhet highway. Shibpur police chief Shamim Ahmed told bdnews24.com the accident at Itakhola area of Sibganj upazila left three dead on the spot. The dead were identified as Belayet Hossain, 35, Mistu Mia, 13, Hamid, 40, and Nazrul Islam, 40. Injured, Suruj Miah, 50, Awlad Hossain, 35, and Saiful, 22, were admitted to Narsinghdi District Hospital and Nur Mohammad, 10, and Nazrul Islam, 24, were taken to Dhaka Medical College Hospital in a critical condition. A case has been filed with the Shibpur police, Ahmed said. In another accident, motorcycle rider Musa was killed and two other co-riders were injured after a pickup van hit the motorcycle on Bholanagar bridge of Narsinghdi, assistant police commissioner Md Shoaib Hossain said. The injured, Mahbub Ullah, 30, and Oli Ullah, 35, were admitted to Narsinghdi District Hospital, he said. Meanwhile, a passenger of a human hauler was killed and two others were injured as an auto rickshaw rammed it from behind. The deceased has been identified as Saleh Ahmed, 50. The injured, Faruk, 28, and Kawsar, 22, were undergoing treatment at Aliganj Health Complex of Chandpur. Hajiganj police sub-inspector Majnu Mia told bdnews24.com the accident caused due to thick fog. bdnews24.com
